SetInCountry: India
Category: Making a local connection
AuthorName: Chandhana  Pd
AuthorCountry: India
Text: "Munnar is a famous hill station in Kerala, India. It is located in the coinfluence\
  \ of three rivers and is elevated  1600m above the sea level. The rolling tea plantations\
  \ and the mist above is a festival of greenary to your eyes indeed! Munar is an\
  \ ideal place to relax with its scenic beauty and can be rightfully called as the\
  \ \u2018Kashmir of kerala\u2019 . It can be a great weekend getaway from the city\u2019\
  s noises into the gorgeous landscape of munar. There several exhilarating  places\
  \ to visit nearby  munar like the best pace where nilakurinji blooms , Marayoor\
  \ which is famous for sandalwood trees , Chinnar Wildlife Sanctuary and Eravikulam\
  \ National Park that offers a great view of diverse wildlife of south India ."
